# Language & Output
- All code, comments, and terminal print statements must be 100% in English.
- No Turkish text anywhere in code or output.

# Stack
- Use LangGraph + LangChain conventions (StateGraph, MessagesState, ToolNode, tools_condition).
- LLM provider: ChatGroq unless explicitly told otherwise.
- Python 3.11+ syntax, type hints required on all function signatures.

# Code Style
- Production-grade: every function has a docstring.
- Tool definitions use the @tool decorator pattern from langchain_core.tools.
- State classes inherit from LangGraph's built-in MessagesState when extending state.
- Prefer explicit node/edge naming over implicit defaults when building graphs.

# Output Behavior
- When generating multi-turn simulations, print clear visual separators (e.g. "=== TURN N ===") so terminal output is easy to read.
- Do not omit error handling for tool calls.